                            <p>You don’t need to be a smart and travel expert to find the affordable international flight deals and there are some easy tips that you need to keep in your mind. </p>
                            <H3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i> Be Flexible with Your Dates: </H3>
                            <p>First of all, flexibility is important while choosing the days and no matter you are flying on a Tuesday, Sunday or Wednesday, but you must know about the right dates for your destination. Tuesday and Wednesday are often much affordable than flying on a Friday or Sunday. If you can change your travel dates by a day or two, then you could see a significant drop in price. </p>
                            <H3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i> book at the right time</H3>
                            <p>Yes, this is another thing, and you must book the flight tickets at the right time and don’t be too late while choosing the good international flight deals. It is essential to book the flight tickets, usually at least 2 to 4 months before the departure date. Pre-booking helps you save at least 40% more on the last-minute flight booking cost. Hence, don’t depend on the last-minute planning and manage your reservation for hotel and flight both at least 2 months before the booking date. </p>
                            <H3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i> Use Fare Comparison Website</H3>
                            <p>Another good tip that you need to follow is to use the fare comparison websites and apps like <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com"><b>Faresmatch</b></a>. This website is your best friend to find the best flight booking deals for international flights. You can search hundreds of airlines and travel sites at once to show you the cheapest options. </p>
                            <H3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i> Fly to Nearby Airports</H3>
                            <p>Yes, you can fly to nearby airports, and sometimes flying into a smaller airport that’s a short bus or train ride away from your final destination can save you a lot of money. The major airports are much more expensive, and always check the options of alternative airports before booking. </p>
                            <H3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i> Check all stopover options. </H3>
